parameters.description: Log of maximum phytoplankton growth rate (V_max, day^-1). This is the maximum rate of nutrient uptake and conversion to biomass by phytoplankton under ideal conditions.
Log of the half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake (K_N, g C m^-3). This is the nutrient concentration at which phytoplankton growth rate is half of its maximum.
Log of the maximum specific grazing rate of zooplankton (g_max, day^-1). This is the maximum rate at which zooplankton can consume phytoplankton.
Log of the half-saturation constant for grazing (K_P, g C m^-3). This is the phytoplankton concentration at which the zooplankton grazing rate is half of its maximum.
Logit of the zooplankton assimilation efficiency (beta, dimensionless). This represents the fraction of grazed phytoplankton that is converted into zooplankton biomass.
Log of the phytoplankton linear mortality rate (m_P, day^-1). This represents losses due to sinking, viral lysis, or other non-grazing mortality.
Log of the zooplankton quadratic mortality rate (m_Z_quad, (g C m^-3)^-1 day^-1). This term represents density-dependent losses, such as predation by higher trophic levels or cannibalism.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of nutrient observations. Represents measurement and process error.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of phytoplankton observations. Represents measurement and process error.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of zooplankton observations. Represents measurement and process error.
